== Reception ==
The game was considered the best pinball simulation ever offered for any home gaming system at the time.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Astrovision's Rising Star: Bally Pin and Galactic Invasion|url=https://ballyalley.com/articles_and_news/Astrovisions%20Rising%20Star/Astrovision's%20Rising%20Star%20(Video)May%201982)(Arcade%20Alley%20column).pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210406080634/https://ballyalley.com/articles_and_news/Astrovisions%20Rising%20Star/Astrovision's%20Rising%20Star%20(Video)May%201982)(Arcade%20Alley%20column).pdf |archive-date=2021-04-06 }}</ref>
Electronic Games magazine called the game skillfully constructed with realistic play and vivid colors.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Electronic Games review of Bally Pin|url=https://ballyalley.com/articles_and_news/Bally%20Pin%20Review/Bally%20Pin%20Review%20(May%201982)(Electronic%20Games).pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210406080757/https://ballyalley.com/articles_and_news/Bally%20Pin%20Review/Bally%20Pin%20Review%20(May%201982)(Electronic%20Games).pdf |archive-date=2021-04-06 }}</ref>

